    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A set of orders of architecture, typically reserved for the five orders of architecture known in ancient Greece and Rome, usually including Ionic, Doric, Corinthian, Composite, and Tuscan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
